{"tid":1596786,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"拆翼行動第一波：提醒英國學校小心處理恐怖份子仔女嘅入學申請","createTime":"2019-09-26T15:57:52.000Z","updateTime":"2019-12-13T14:02:39.000Z","uid":327188,"like":23,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"074c40638a326961d64a559ec4c6542dd475a3d1","tid":1596786,"uid":327188,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T15:57:52.000Z","msg":"拆翼行動第一波對象：英國教育官員。<br />\n<br />\n此行動旨在響應黑社會大佬何妖嘅呼籲，鼓勵恐怖份子仔女去大灣區讀書，唔好去英美加澳勾結外國勢力。我借用陳淑莊響聯合國嘅演詞，寫咗電郵，乞求英國學校小心處理垃圾狗仔狗女嘅入學申請。<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: red;\">請大家幫忙花一分鐘發電郵俾英國教育大臣同埋英國教育部長，也請廣傳。<br />\n</span></strong><br />\n拆翼行動仲會有好多波，但係我實在好鬼忙，太多課外活動。如果見到恐怖份子多啲，心情唔靚，行動就會出得密啲。歡迎大家遍地開花，修改電郵，寄俾其他相關人士和部門。<br />\n<br />\n拆翼行動下一波預告：所有英國共二萬多間中小學。<br />\n<br />\nTo: gavin.williamson.mp@parliament.uk; permanent.secretary@education.gov.uk; educom@parliament.uk<br />\n<br />\nSubject: IMPORTANT: Caution Against Applications from Hong Kong Students<br />\n<br />\nDear Mr. Williamson and Mr. Slater:<br />\n<br />\nI am writing to suggest all schools in the United Kingdom exercising extreme caution in reviewing admission applications from Hong Kong students, with respect to whether their parents are police officers, which should be carefully verified and considered in the assessment.<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong is on the verge of a humanitarian crisis, as police brutality against supporters of the democratic movement escalates.<br />\n<br />\nArrested protesters face physical abuse and humiliation by the police. A female protester openly spoke of an unnecessary and degrading strip search she went through. More sexual abuse cases remain unreported. Detained protesters were denied timely access to medical and legal assistance.<br />\n<br />\nUse of force is excessive and indiscriminate. The police shot a beanbag round at a first-aider and blinded one of her eyes. The riot police attacked innocent subway passengers whom they claimed were rioters in disguise. As of now the police have fired more than 3,000 tear gas cans, many of which had expired and might have turned chemically dangerous to human health.<br />\n<br />\nThe police call protesters &ldquo;cockroaches&rdquo;. Brutal crackdowns and pre-emptive violence against them are hence regarded as acceptable pest control to curb free speech.<br />\n<br />\nThere are now international efforts, such as the Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act of 2019 to be passed in the US, trying to sanction Hong Kong police and classify them as terrorists. If justice does exist in our world, they will be eventually prosecuted by legal authorities including the International Crime Court for crimes against humanity. <br />\n<br />\nHaving committed war crimes, the police are worried about the safety of their children, who are now carrying personal alarms all the time, inside and outside schools. They are urgently sending their children to schools overseas, particularly the UK, as reported by Chinese-language newspapers Apple Daily on September 23: <a href=\"https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/daily/article/20190923/20773403\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Flocal%2Fdaily%2Farticle%2F20190923%2F20773403&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=26a36def\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Flocal%2Fdaily%2Farticle%2F20190923%2F20773403&h=29000982\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/daily/article/20190923/20773403</a><br />\n<br />\nAs a result, in reviewing applications from Hong Kong students with police parents, all schools in the United Kingdom may want to consider whether the applicants appreciate liberty and justice, whether they will make conflicts with their classmates, whether they will harm the school reputation, and whether they will be able to pay school fees as their parents will be jailed.<br />\n<br />\nThank you very much for your kind attention.<br />\n<br />\nYours faithfully,<br />\n<br />\nOne of the many Hong Kong citizens under the threat of life from the police<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nP.S. A few of the many reports on police brutality:<br />\n<br />\nNew York Times: A Man or a &lsquo;Yellow Object&rsquo;? Hong Kong Police Dispute Assault Allegations<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/24/world/asia/hong-kong-yellow-object.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F24%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fhong-kong-yellow-object.html&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=d7ed6f5e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/24/world/asia/hong-kong-yellow-object.html</a><br />\n<br />\nNew York Times: Police Dressed as Protesters: How Undercover Police in Hong Kong Severely Injured People<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/22/world/hong-kong-police-protests.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F22%2Fworld%2Fhong-kong-police-protests.html&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=b6a467a2\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/22/world/hong-kong-police-protests.html</a><br />\n<br />\nNew York Times: Did Hong Kong Police Abuse Protesters? What Videos Show<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/30/world/asia/did-hong-kong-police-abuse-protesters-what-videos-show.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F06%2F30%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fdid-hong-kong-police-abuse-protesters-what-videos-show.html&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=6883c2df\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/30/world/asia/did-hong-kong-police-abuse-protesters-what-videos-show.html</a><br />\n<br />\nNew York Times: Two 13-Year-Olds Are Arrested Over Hong Kong Protests<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/22/world/asia/hong-kong-protests.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F22%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fhong-kong-protests.html&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=d15f4742\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/22/world/asia/hong-kong-protests.html</a><br />\n<br />\nSCMP: Hong Kong police provide personal alarms to children of officers in response to cyberbullying and threats of attack amid worsening protest violence<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3025159/hong-kong-police-provide-personal-alarms-children\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fhong-kong%2Flaw-and-crime%2Farticle%2F3025159%2Fhong-kong-police-provide-personal-alarms-children&d=0M2zeZ419d%2BEsiU1FPoAw8wCZVYJieBIKSEfzXA%2FSmA%3D&h=68ca3bab\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3025159/hong-kong-police-provide-personal-alarms-children</a>"},{"pid":"088542d361eb1bea68eed2a237a2596d9b48e56f","tid":1596786,"uid":307203,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T15:58:21.000Z","msg":"push<br />\n<br />\n[文宣] 我哋好似忘記咗其中一條重要戰線<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1592692\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1592692</a><br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區"},{"pid":"b384b99de3a505e4bc6e3df26cb179e30cc86d09","tid":1596786,"uid":327188,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T15:58:29.000Z","msg":"自推"},{"pid":"f02a723719bda7d24a74462a7527ff60c577b02d","tid":1596786,"uid":327188,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T15:59:07.000Z","msg":"自推"},{"pid":"6435abd23e0028cad2a53ff323d18967274260e6","tid":1596786,"uid":286778,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T16:05:45.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"bd0ff41a355a780020f91129aa8761cf0b3b5abd","tid":1596786,"uid":158766,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-26T16:08:20.000Z","msg":"香港警察鎮